": \"transgender and intersex women\", \"from\": 3569, \"to\": 3599}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But it also is part of a long history.\", \"from\": 3601, \"to\": 3639, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 3616, \"to\": 3620}, {\"ngram\": \"a long history\", \"from\": 3624, \"to\": 3638}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For as long as women's sports have existed, there has been monitoring of who gets to participate.\", \"from\": 3640, \"to\": 3737, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"women's sports\", \"from\": 3655, \"to\": 3669}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sex verification testing and regulating eligibility for the women's category has historically fallen into four buckets: looking for cisgender men masquerading as women, policing doping, creating policy for intersex athletes and those with differences in sex development and creating policy for transgender athletes.\", \"from\": 3739, \"to\": 4054, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Sex verification testing\", \"from\": 3739, \"to\": 3763}, {\"ngram\": \"eligibility\", \"from\": 3779, \"to\": 3790}, {\"ngram\": \"the women's category\", \"from\": 3795, \"to\": 3815}, {\"ngram\": \"four buckets\", \"from\": 3845, \"to\": 3857}, {\"ngram\": \"cisgender men\", \"from\": 3871, \"to\": 3884}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 3901, \"to\": 3906}, {\"ngram\": \"doping\", \"from\": 3917, \"to\": 3923}, {\"ngram\": \"policy\", \"from\": 3934, \"to\": 3940}, {\"ngram\": \"intersex athletes\", \"from\": 3945, \"to\": 3962}, {\"ngram\": \"differences\", \"from\": 3978, \"to\": 3989}, {\"ngram\": \"sex development\", \"from\": 3993, \"to\": 4008}, {\"ngram\": \"policy\", \"from\": 4022, \"to\": 4028}, {\"ngram\": \"transgender athletes\", \"from\": 4033, \"to\": 4053}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At the core of these issues is the desire to pursue fairness and to regulate what many see as possible unfair advantages.\", \"from\": 4056, \"to\": 4177, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the core\", \"from\": 4059, \"to\": 4067}, {\"ngram\": \"these issues\", \"from\": 4071, \"to\": 4083}, {\"ngram\": \"the desire\", \"from\": 4087, \"to\": 4097}, {\"ngram\": \"fairness\", \"from\": 4108, \"to\": 4116}, {\"ngram\": \"possible unfair advantages\", \"from\": 4150, \"to\": 4176}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This has taken multiple forms, but testosterone levels and testosterone-driven puberty have become the focal point of policy in recent years.\", \"from\": 4178, \"to\": 4319, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"multiple forms\", \"from\": 4193, \"to\": 4207}, {\"ngram\": \"testosterone levels\", \"from\": 4213, \"to\": 4232}, {\"ngram\": \"testosterone-driven puberty\", \"from\": 4237, \"to\": 4264}, {\"ngram\": \"the focal point\", \"from\": 4277, \"to\": 4292}, {\"ngram\": \"policy\", \"from\": 4296, \"to\": 4302}, {\"ngram\": \"recent years\", \"from\": 4306, \"to\": 4318}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Testosterone is a hormone that is typically substantially higher in those assigned male at birth and who have experienced puberty.\", \"from\": 4320, \"to\": 4450, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4320, \"end\": 4332, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Testosterone\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.943518497500862e-104, \"text\": \"Testosterone\", \"types\": [\"Q11173\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Testosterone\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Testosterone\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a hormone\", \"from\": 4336, \"to\": 4345}, {\"ngram\": \"those assigned male\", \"from\": 4388, \"to\": 4407}, {\"ngram\": \"birth\", \"from\": 4411, \"to\": 4416}, {\"ngram\": \"puberty\", \"from\": 4442, \"to\": 4449}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Testosterone can provide metabolic and physiological advantages such as greater speed and the ability to build muscle mass.\", \"from\": 4451, \"to\": 4574, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4451, \"end\": 4463, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Testosterone\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.943518497500862e-104, \"text\": \"Testosterone\", \"types\": [\"Q11173\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Testosterone\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Testosterone\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"metabolic and physiological advantages\", \"from\": 4476, \"to\": 4514}, {\"ngram\": \"greater speed\", \"from\": 4523, \"to\": 4536}, {\"ngram\": \"the ability\", \"from\": 4541, \"to\": 4552}, {\"ngram\": \"muscle mass\", \"from\": 4562, \"to\": 4573}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Differences in sex development (DSD) or intersex traits describe a group of conditions that are statistically atypical from the norm when it comes to biological sex.\", \"from\": 4576, \"to\": 4741, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4608, \"end\": 4611, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Signals_Directorate\", \"score\": 0.9999470090095144, \"rank\": 5.299379889342907e-05, \"text\": \"DSD\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Signals_Directorate\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Signals_Directorate\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Differences\", \"from\": 4576, \"to\": 4587}, {\"ngram\": \"sex development\", \"from\": 4591, \"to\": 4606}, {\"ngram\": \"intersex traits\", \"from\": 4616, \"to\": 4631}, {\"ngram\": \"a group\", \"from\": 4641, \"to\": 4648}, {\"ngram\": \"conditions\", \"from\": 4652, \"to\": 4662}, {\"ngram\": \"the norm\", \"from\": 4700, \"to\": 4708}, {\"ngram\": \"biological sex\", \"from\": 4726, \"to\": 4740}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"These are individuals who have a hormonal or genetic condition where they have characteristics of both male and female,\\\" endocrinologist and former IOC consultant Dr. Myron Genel said.\", \"from\": 4742, \"to\": 4927, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4910, \"end\": 4915, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Myron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2522697506024015e-14, \"text\": \"Myron\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Myron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Myron\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"individuals\", \"from\": 4753, \"to\": 4764}, {\"ngram\": \"a hormonal or genetic condition\", \"from\": 4774, \"to\": 4805}, {\"ngram\": \"characteristics\", \"from\": 4822, \"to\": 4837}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sometimes differences in sex development can result in higher levels of testosterone.\", \"from\": 4928, \"to\": 5013, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"differences\", \"from\": 4938, \"to\": 4949}, {\"ngram\": \"sex development\", \"from\": 4953, \"to\": 4968}, {\"ngram\": \"higher levels\", \"from\": 4983, \"to\": 4996}, {\"ngram\": \"testosterone\", \"from\": 5000, \"to\": 5012}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Athletes competing in women's sports with those types of DSD are a focus of policymakers because of the concern that higher testosterone could confer a competitive advantage.\", \"from\": 5014, \"to\": 5188, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5071, \"end\": 5074, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Signals_Directorate\", \"score\": 0.9999470090095144, \"rank\": 5.299379889342907e-05, \"text\": \"DSD\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Signals_Directorate\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Signals_Directorate\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Athletes\", \"from\": 5014, \"to\": 5022}, {\"ngram\": \"women's sports\", \"from\": 5036, \"to\": 5050}, {\"ngram\": \"those types\", \"from\": 5056, \"to\": 5067}, {\"ngram\": \"a focus\", \"from\": 5079, \"to\": 5086}, {\"ngram\": \"policymakers\", \"from\": 5090, \"to\": 5102}, {\"ngram\": \"the concern\", \"from\": 5114, \"to\": 5125}, {\"ngram\": \"higher testosterone\", \"from\": 5131, \"to\": 5150}, {\"ngram\": \"a competitive advantage\", \"from\": 5164, \"to\": 5187}]}, {\"sentence\": \"An example is someone who is partially or completely insensitive to androgens, such as testosterone.\", \"from\": 5190, \"to\": 5290, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"An example\", \"from\": 5190, \"to\": 5200}, {\"ngram\": \"someone\", \"from\": 5204, \"to\": 5211}, {\"ngram\": \"androgens\", \"from\": 5258, \"to\": 5267}, {\"ngram\": \"testosterone\", \"from\": 5277, \"to\": 5289}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They may be assigned female at birth but have XY chromosomes because of their body's physiological insensitivity to androgens.\", \"from\": 5291, \"to\": 5417, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"female\", \"from\": 5312, \"to\": 5318}, {\"ngram\": \"birth\", \"from\": 5322, \"to\": 5327}, {\"ngram\": \"XY chromosomes\", \"from\": 5337, \"to\": 5351}, {\"ngram\": \"their body's physiological insensitivity\", \"from\": 5363, \"to\": 5403}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A person with XY chromosomes who has a difference of sex development may not present with characteristics associated with maleness and therefore can be assigned female at birth and identify as a woman.\", \"from\": 5419, \"to\": 5620, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5433, \"end\": 5447, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/XY_sex-determination_system\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"XY chromosomes\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/XY_sex-determination_system\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/XY_sex-determination_system\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A person\", \"from\": 5419, \"to\": 5427}, {\"ngram\": \"a difference\", \"from\": 5456, \"to\": 5468}, {\"ngram\": \"sex development\", \"from\": 5472, \"to\": 5487}, {\"ngram\": \"characteristics\", \"from\": 5509, \"to\": 5524}, {\"ngram\": \"maleness\", \"from\": 5541, \"to\": 5549}, {\"ngram\": \"female\", \"from\": 5580, \"to\": 5586}, {\"ngram\": \"birth\", \"from\": 5590, \"to\": 5595}, {\"ngram\": \"a woman\", \"from\": 5612, \"to\": 5619}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sometimes these conditions are lumped together as \\\"46 XY DSD.\\\"\", \"from\": 5621, \"to\": 5683, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"these conditions\", \"from\": 5631, \"to\": 5647}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"46 XY DSD\", \"from\": 5671, \"to\": 5681}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Forty-six is the typical number of chromosomes, XY refers to the chromosomes present and DSD stands for differences of sex development.\", \"from\": 5684, \"to\": 5819, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5773, \"end\": 5776, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Signals_Directorate\", \"score\": 0.9999470090095144, \"rank\": 5.299379889342907e-05, \"text\": \"DSD\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Signals_Directorate\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Signals_Directorate\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the typical number\", \"from\": 5697, \"to\": 5715}, {\"ngram\": \"chromosomes\", \"from\": 5719, \"to\": 5730}, {\"ngram\": \"XY\", \"from\": 5732, \"to\": 5734}, {\"ngram\": \"the chromosomes\", \"from\": 5745, \"to\": 5760}, {\"ngram\": \"differences\", \"from\": 5788, \"to\": 5799}, {\"ngram\": \"sex development\", \"from\": 5803, \"to\": 5818}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There is a difference between transgender athletes and intersex athletes.\", \"from\": 5821, \"to\": 5894, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a difference\", \"from\": 5830, \"to\": 5842}, {\"ngram\": \"transgender athletes\", \"from\": 5851, \"to\": 5871}, {\"ngram\": \"intersex athletes\", \"from\": 5876, \"to\": 5893}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Someone who is transgender has a gender identity that is not in alignment with their sex, and they may or may not medically transition to address that dysphoria.\", \"from\": 5895, \"to\": 6056, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Someone\", \"from\": 5895, \"to\": 5902}, {\"ngram\": \"a gender identity\", \"from\": 5926, \"to\": 5943}, {\"ngram\": \"alignment\", \"from\": 5959, \"to\": 5968}, {\"ngram\": \"their sex\", \"from\": 5974, \"to\": 5983}, {\"ngram\": \"may not medically transition\", \"from\": 6001, \"to\": 6029}, {\"ngram\": \"that dysphoria\", \"from\": 6041, \"to\": 6055}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Policy regulating eligibility for women's sports can address both of these populations, but in the case of Khelif and Lin, it's unclear if such policy would even apply.\", \"from\": 6058, \"to\": 6226, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Policy regulating eligibility\", \"from\": 6058, \"to\": 6087}, {\"ngram\": \"women's sports\", \"from\": 6092, \"to\": 6106}, {\"ngram\": \"these populations\", \"from\": 6127, \"to\": 6144}, {\"ngram\": \"the case\", \"from\": 6153, \"to\": 6161}, {\"ngram\": \"Khelif\", \"from\": 6165, \"to\": 6171}, {\"ngram\": \"Lin\", \"from\": 6176, \"to\": 6179}, {\"ngram\": \"such policy\", \"from\": 6197, \"to\": 6208}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There is no evidence that either boxer is transgender, and beyond the failed IBA tests, there is little to no evidence that either athlete has a difference in sex development.\", \"from\": 6227, \"to\": 6402, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6304, \"end\": 6307, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"score\": 0.9999983739594005, \"rank\": 1.6260436092435352e-06, \"text\": \"IBA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"no evidence\", \"from\": 6236, \"to\": 6247}, {\"ngram\": \"either boxer\", \"from\": 6253, \"to\": 6265}, {\"ngram\": \"no evidence\", \"from\": 6334, \"to\": 6345}, {\"ngram\": \"either athlete\", \"from\": 6351, \"to\": 6365}, {\"ngram\": \"a difference\", \"from\": 6370, \"to\": 6382}, {\"ngram\": \"sex development\", \"from\": 6386, \"to\": 6401}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"There has been some confusion that somehow it's a man fighting a woman, this is just not the case,\\\" IOC spokesperson Mark Adams said about the Khelif-Carini bout in a news conference on Thursday.\", \"from\": 6404, \"to\": 6600, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6522, \"end\": 6532, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mark_Adams_(basketball,_born_May_1956)\", \"score\": 0.5137413298826524, \"rank\": 0.45833333333321225, \"text\": \"Mark Adams\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mark_Adams_(basketball,_born_May_1956)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mark_Adams_(basketball,_born_May_1956)\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"some confusion\", \"from\": 6420, \"to\": 6434}, {\"ngram\": \"a man\", \"from\": 6453, \"to\": 6458}, {\"ngram\": \"a woman\", \"from\": 6468, \"to\": 6475}, {\"ngram\": \"the case\", \"from\": 6494, \"to\": 6502}, {\"ngram\": \"the Khelif-Carini bout\", \"from\": 6544, \"to\": 6566}, {\"ngram\": \"a news conference\", \"from\": 6570, \"to\": 6587}, {\"ngram\": \"Thursday\", \"from\": 6591, \"to\": 6599}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"On that, there is consensus.\", \"from\": 6601, \"to\": 6630, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"consensus\", \"from\": 6620, \"to\": 6629}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Scientifically this is not a man fighting a woman.\\\"\", \"from\": 6631, \"to\": 6682, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a man\", \"from\": 6658, \"to\": 6663}, {\"ngram\": \"a woman\", \"from\": 6673, \"to\": 6680}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The fight between Khelif and Carini and the subsequent outrage hearkens back to South African runner Caster Semenya's experience in Berlin at the 2009 track and field world championships.\", \"from\": 6684, \"to\": 6871, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6713, \"end\": 6719, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carini\", \"score\": 0.9994616318386671, \"rank\": 0.0005386581578890087, \"text\": \"Carini\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carini\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carini\"}, {\"begin\": 6785, \"end\": 6799, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caster_Semenya\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Caster Semenya\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caster_Semenya\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caster_Semenya\"}, {\"begin\": 6816, \"end\": 6822, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Berlin\", \"score\": 0.9999994876717613, \"rank\": 5.077526063416151e-07, \"text\": \"Berlin\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Berlin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Berlin\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The fight\", \"from\": 6684, \"to\": 6693}, {\"ngram\": \"Khelif\", \"from\": 6702, \"to\": 6708}, {\"ngram\": \"the subsequent outrage\", \"from\": 6724, \"to\": 6746}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2009 track and field world championships\", \"from\": 6826, \"to\": 6870}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After crossing the finish line first in the 800 meters, Semenya was whisked away for a sex verification exam since her gender was questioned.\", \"from\": 6872, \"to\": 7013, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the finish line\", \"from\": 6887, \"to\": 6902}, {\"ngram\": \"the 800 meters\", \"from\": 6912, \"to\": 6926}, {\"ngram\": \"Semenya\", \"from\": 6928, \"to\": 6935}, {\"ngram\": \"a sex verification exam\", \"from\": 6957, \"to\": 6980}, {\"ngram\": \"her gender\", \"from\": 6987, \"to\": 6997}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The moment began a nearly 15-year battle between the South African middle-distance runner and World Athletics over her eligibility and that of other athletes like her.\", \"from\": 7014, \"to\": 7181, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7108, \"end\": 7123, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.727600132869888e-38, \"text\": \"World Athletics\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The moment\", \"from\": 7014, \"to\": 7024}, {\"ngram\": \"a nearly 15-year battle\", \"from\": 7031, \"to\": 7054}, {\"ngram\": \"the South African middle-distance runner\", \"from\": 7063, \"to\": 7103}, {\"ngram\": \"her eligibility\", \"from\": 7129, \"to\": 7144}, {\"ngram\": \"other athletes\", \"from\": 7157, \"to\": 7171}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Following Semenya's win in Berlin, World Athletics (then IAAF) instituted policies that required Semenya to medically lower her testosterone, a process she described in an interview with Andrea Kremer as making her sick.\", \"from\": 7183, \"to\": 7403, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7210, \"end\": 7216, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Berlin\", \"score\": 0.9999994876717613, \"rank\": 5.077526063416151e-07, \"text\": \"Berlin\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Berlin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Berlin\"}, {\"begin\": 7218, \"end\": 7233, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.727600132869888e-38, \"text\": \"World Athletics\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\"}, {\"begin\": 7370, \"end\": 7383, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrea_Kremer\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Andrea Kremer\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrea_Kremer\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrea_Kremer\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Semenya's win\", \"from\": 7193, \"to\": 7206}, {\"ngram\": \"(then IAAF\", \"from\": 7234, \"to\": 7244}, {\"ngram\": \"policies\", \"from\": 7257, \"to\": 7265}, {\"ngram\": \"Semenya\", \"from\": 7280, \"to\": 7287}, {\"ngram\": \"her testosterone\", \"from\": 7307, \"to\": 7323}, {\"ngram\": \"a process\", \"from\": 7325, \"to\": 7334}, {\"ngram\": \"an interview\", \"from\": 7352, \"to\": 7364}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Made me gain weight,\\\" Semenya said.\", \"from\": 7404, \"to\": 7440, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"weight\", \"from\": 7418, \"to\": 7424}, {\"ngram\": \"Semenya\", \"from\": 7427, \"to\": 7434}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Panic attacks.\", \"from\": 7441, \"to\": 7456, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"\\\"Panic attacks\", \"from\": 7441, \"to\": 7455}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's like stabbing yourself with a knife every day, but I had no choice.\", \"from\": 7457, \"to\": 7529, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a knife\", \"from\": 7490, \"to\": 7497}, {\"ngram\": \"no choice\", \"from\": 7519, \"to\": 7528}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I am 18 and I want to run.\\\"\", \"from\": 7530, \"to\": 7557, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She returned to competition in 2010 and competed in 2012 at the London Olympics, where she finished second in the 800 but was elevated to gold following the disqualification of Mariya Savinova for doping.\", \"from\": 7559, \"to\": 7763, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7623, \"end\": 7638, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.589256105411703e-21, \"text\": \"London Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 7736, \"end\": 7751, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mariya_Savinova\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mariya Savinova\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mariya_Savinova\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mariya_Savinova\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"competition\", \"from\": 7575, \"to\": 7586}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 7697, \"to\": 7701}, {\"ngram\": \"the disqualification\", \"from\": 7712, \"to\": 7732}, {\"ngram\": \"doping\", \"from\": 7756, \"to\": 7762}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In 2015, Indian sprinter Dutee Chand challenged the World Athletics testosterone requirements at the Court of Arbitration for Sport (CAS), which ruled in her favor.\", \"from\": 7764, \"to\": 7928, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7773, \"end\": 7779, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Native_Americans_in_the_United_States\", \"score\": 0.8133490422274096, \"rank\": 0.20819880905910884, \"text\": \"Indian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Native_Americans_in_the_United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Native_Americans_in_the_United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 7789, \"end\": 7800, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutee_Chand\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Dutee Chand\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutee_Chand\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutee_Chand\"}, {\"begin\": 7816, \"end\": 7831, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.727600132869888e-38, \"text\": \"World Athletics\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Court\", \"from\": 7861, \"to\": 7870}, {\"ngram\": \"Arbitration\", \"from\": 7874, \"to\": 7885}, {\"ngram\": \"Sport\", \"from\": 7890, \"to\": 7895}, {\"ngram\": \"CAS\", \"from\": 7897, \"to\": 7900}, {\"ngram\": \"her favor\", \"from\": 7918, \"to\": 7927}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That allowed both her and Semenya to compete in the 2016 Olympics without reducing their testosterone levels.\", \"from\": 7929, \"to\": 8038, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Semenya\", \"from\": 7955, \"to\": 7962}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2016 Olympics\", \"from\": 7977, \"to\": 7994}, {\"ngram\": \"their testosterone levels\", \"from\": 8012, \"to\": 8037}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Chand did not advance beyond the 100-meter heats.\", \"from\": 8039, \"to\": 8088, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Chand\", \"from\": 8039, \"to\": 8044}, {\"ngram\": \"the 100-meter heats\", \"from\": 8068, \"to\": 8087}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Semenya won gold in the 800.\", \"from\": 8089, \"to\": 8117, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Semenya\", \"from\": 8089, \"to\": 8096}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 8101, \"to\": 8105}]}, {\"sentence\": \"New regulations were adopted in 2018 that affected Semenya's events and would have required her to medically lower her testosterone levels to stay eligible.\", \"from\": 8119, \"to\": 8275, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"New regulations\", \"from\": 8119, \"to\": 8134}, {\"ngram\": \"Semenya's events\", \"from\": 8170, \"to\": 8186}, {\"ngram\": \"her testosterone levels\", \"from\": 8234, \"to\": 8257}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She challenged the rules at CAS.\", \"from\": 8276, \"to\": 8308, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8304, \"end\": 8307, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Court_of_Arbitration_for_Sport\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.127765703442088e-60, \"text\": \"CAS\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Court_of_Arbitration_for_Sport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Court_of_Arbitration_for_Sport\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the rules\", \"from\": 8291, \"to\": 8300}]}, {\"sentence\": \"During the hearing, World Athletics argued that theoverrepresentation of athletes with DSDin elite women's athletics speaks to the advantage present.\", \"from\": 8309, \"to\": 8458, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8329, \"end\": 8344, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.727600132869888e-38, \"text\": \"World Athletics\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the hearing\", \"from\": 8316, \"to\": 8327}, {\"ngram\": \"theoverrepresentation\", \"from\": 8357, \"to\": 8378}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 8382, \"to\": 8390}, {\"ngram\": \"DSDin elite women's athletics\", \"from\": 8396, \"to\": 8425}, {\"ngram\": \"the advantage present\", \"from\": 8436, \"to\": 8457}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Approximately 1 in 20,000 of the general population have a 46 XY DSD,\\\" the organization argued.\", \"from\": 8459, \"to\": 8555, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the general population\", \"from\": 8489, \"to\": 8511}, {\"ngram\": \"a 46 XY DSD\", \"from\": 8517, \"to\": 8528}, {\"ngram\": \"the organization\", \"from\": 8531, \"to\": 8547}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"In elite women's competition, however, the proportion is approximately 7 in 1,000 -- a prevalence that is 140 times higher.\", \"from\": 8556, \"to\": 8680, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"elite women's competition\", \"from\": 8560, \"to\": 8585}, {\"ngram\": \"the proportion\", \"from\": 8596, \"to\": 8610}, {\"ngram\": \"a prevalence\", \"from\": 8642, \"to\": 8654}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This is strong evidence of a performance advantage.\\\"\", \"from\": 8681, \"to\": 8733, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"strong evidence\", \"from\": 8689, \"to\": 8704}, {\"ngram\": \"a performance advantage\", \"from\": 8708, \"to\": 8731}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Semenya lost her legal battle.\", \"from\": 8735, \"to\": 8765, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Semenya\", \"from\": 8735, \"to\": 8742}, {\"ngram\": \"her legal battle\", \"from\": 8748, \"to\": 8764}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She chose not to medicate and therefore was ineligible to compete in her preferred events in the Tokyo Olympics, effectively ending her career.\", \"from\": 8766, \"to\": 8909, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"her preferred events\", \"from\": 8835, \"to\": 8855}, {\"ngram\": \"the Tokyo Olympics\", \"from\": 8859, \"to\": 8877}, {\"ngram\": \"her career\", \"from\": 8898, \"to\": 8908}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The study World Athletics used to inform its argument was published in 2017 in the British Journal of Sports Medicine.\", \"from\": 8911, \"to\": 9029, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8921, \"end\": 8936, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.727600132869888e-38, \"text\": \"World Athletics\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The study\", \"from\": 8911, \"to\": 8920}, {\"ngram\": \"its argument\", \"from\": 8952, \"to\": 8964}, {\"ngram\": \"the British Journal\", \"from\": 8990, \"to\": 9009}, {\"ngram\": \"Sports Medicine\", \"from\": 9013, \"to\": 9028}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Four years after it was published, the journal issued a correction, saying, \\\"There is no confirmatory evidence for causality in the observed relationships reported.\\\"\", \"from\": 9030, \"to\": 9195, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the journal\", \"from\": 9065, \"to\": 9076}, {\"ngram\": \"a correction\", \"from\": 9084, \"to\": 9096}, {\"ngram\": \"no confirmatory evidence\", \"from\": 9116, \"to\": 9140}, {\"ngram\": \"causality\", \"from\": 9145, \"to\": 9154}, {\"ngram\": \"the observed relationships\", \"from\": 9158, \"to\": 9184}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In plain English: the paper, funded by World Athletics, failed to scientifically prove the relationship between higher testosterone levels in female athletes and a performance advantage.\", \"from\": 9196, \"to\": 9382, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9235, \"end\": 9250, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.727600132869888e-38, \"text\": \"World Athletics\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"plain English\", \"from\": 9199, \"to\": 9212}, {\"ngram\": \"the paper\", \"from\": 9214, \"to\": 9223}, {\"ngram\": \"the relationship\", \"from\": 9283, \"to\": 9299}, {\"ngram\": \"higher testosterone levels\", \"from\": 9308, \"to\": 9334}, {\"ngram\": \"female athletes\", \"from\": 9338, \"to\": 9353}, {\"ngram\": \"a performance advantage\", \"from\": 9358, \"to\": 9381}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I feel that [World Athletics] has confiscated a large part of my life,\\\" Semenya wrote in her memoir, \\\"The Race to Be Myself.\\\"\", \"from\": 9384, \"to\": 9510, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9398, \"end\": 9413, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.727600132869888e-38, \"text\": \"World Athletics\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a large part\", \"from\": 9431, \"to\": 9443}, {\"ngram\": \"my life\", \"from\": 9447, \"to\": 9454}, {\"ngram\": \"Semenya\", \"from\": 9457, \"to\": 9464}, {\"ngram\": \"her memoir\", \"from\": 9474, \"to\": 9484}, {\"ngram\": \"The Race\", \"from\": 9487, \"to\": 9495}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I have spent as much time fighting them as I have training and racing.\", \"from\": 9511, \"to\": 9582, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"as much time\", \"from\": 9525, \"to\": 9537}, {\"ngram\": \"training\", \"from\": 9562, \"to\": 9570}, {\"ngram\": \"racing\", \"from\": 9575, \"to\": 9581}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They have stolen years of performances not only from me but also from the audience.\\\"\", \"from\": 9583, \"to\": 9667, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"years\", \"from\": 9600, \"to\": 9605}, {\"ngram\": \"performances\", \"from\": 9609, \"to\": 9621}, {\"ngram\": \"the audience\", \"from\": 9653, \"to\": 9665}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The regulations that have kept Semenya from competing have also impacted other athletes, such as the 800-meter silver medalist at the Rio 2016 Olympics,Francine Niyonsaba.\", \"from\": 9669, \"to\": 9840, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9803, \"end\": 9806, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.085988127598147e-20, \"text\": \"Rio\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 9807, \"end\": 9820, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.8199902871887821e-44, \"text\": \"2016 Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 9821, \"end\": 9839, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Francine_Niyonsaba\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Francine Niyonsaba\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Francine_Niyonsaba\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Francine_Niyonsaba\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The regulations\", \"from\": 9669, \"to\": 9684}, {\"ngram\": \"Semenya\", \"from\": 9700, \"to\": 9707}, {\"ngram\": \"other athletes\", \"from\": 9742, \"to\": 9756}, {\"ngram\": \"the 800-meter silver medalist\", \"from\": 9766, \"to\": 9795}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The controversy surrounding Khelif and Lin is the first around DSD athletes in combat sports at the Olympics.\", \"from\": 9842, \"to\": 9951, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9905, \"end\": 9908, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Signals_Directorate\", \"score\": 0.9999470090095144, \"rank\": 5.299379889342907e-05, \"text\": \"DSD\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Signals_Directorate\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Signals_Directorate\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The controversy\", \"from\": 9842, \"to\": 9857}, {\"ngram\": \"Khelif\", \"from\": 9870, \"to\": 9876}, {\"ngram\": \"Lin\", \"from\": 9881, \"to\": 9884}, {\"ngram\": \"combat sports\", \"from\": 9921, \"to\": 9934}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 9938, \"to\": 9950}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There have been examples of transgender athletes competing in lower levels, such as Fallon Fox in mixed martial arts and Mack Beggs in high school girls wrestling, but neither of those examples are good comparisons because neither Khelif nor Lin is known to be transgender.\", \"from\": 9952, \"to\": 10225, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10036, \"end\": 10046, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fallon_Fox\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Fallon Fox\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fallon_Fox\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fallon_Fox\"}, {\"begin\": 10073, \"end\": 10083, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mack_Beggs\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mack Beggs\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mack_Beggs\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mack_Beggs\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"examples\", \"from\": 9968, \"to\": 9976}, {\"ngram\": \"transgender athletes\", \"from\": 9980, \"to\": 10000}, {\"ngram\": \"lower levels\", \"from\": 10014, \"to\": 10026}, {\"ngram\": \"mixed martial arts\", \"from\": 10050, \"to\": 10068}, {\"ngram\": \"high school girls wrestling\", \"from\": 10087, \"to\": 10114}, {\"ngram\": \"neither\", \"from\": 10120, \"to\": 10127}, {\"ngram\": \"those examples\", \"from\": 10131, \"to\": 10145}, {\"ngram\": \"good comparisons\", \"from\": 10150, \"to\": 10166}, {\"ngram\": \"neither Khelif\", \"from\": 10175, \"to\": 10189}, {\"ngram\": \"Lin\", \"from\": 10194, \"to\": 10197}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Regulating women's sports, however, has been happening for as long as the category has existed.\", \"from\": 10227, \"to\": 10322, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"women's sports\", \"from\": 10238, \"to\": 10252}, {\"ngram\": \"the category\", \"from\": 10297, \"to\": 10309}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When the modern Olympics began in 1896, women were not allowed to participate.\", \"from\": 10323, \"to\": 10401, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the modern Olympics\", \"from\": 10328, \"to\": 10347}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 10363, \"to\": 10368}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Women did compete in Paris in 1900 and, as women's sports grew, sport governing bodies began exploring sex verification testing for women's competitions.\", \"from\": 10402, \"to\": 10555, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10423, \"end\": 10428, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 9.187505902325563e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Women\", \"from\": 10402, \"to\": 10407}, {\"ngram\": \"women's sports\", \"from\": 10445, \"to\": 10459}, {\"ngram\": \"sport governing bodies\", \"from\": 10466, \"to\": 10488}, {\"ngram\": \"sex verification testing\", \"from\": 10505, \"to\": 10529}, {\"ngram\": \"women's competitions\", \"from\": 10534, \"to\": 10554}]}, {\"sentence\": \"An early flashpoint emerged in the 1930s after Zden\\u011bk Koubek, an athlete from what was then Czechoslovakia, began publicly identifying as a man.\", \"from\": 10556, \"to\": 10700, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10603, \"end\": 10616, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zden\\u011bk_Koubek\", \"score\": 0.9999999516758192, \"rank\": 0.0, \"te